Privacy Policy

Last Updated: April 2024

1. DATA COLLECTION

Firefox Chromecast Ultimate ("the Extension") does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information to external servers. All data processing occurs locally on your device.

2. LOCAL NETWORK DATA

The Extension communicates with the ChromecastUltimate Android application on your local network to discover and control Chromecast devices. This communication stays within your local network and is not transmitted externally.

3. DATA USAGE

The Extension processes the following data locally:
- Current tab URL (when casting)
- Device discovery results from local network
- Server connection settings (stored locally in your browser)

4. THIRD-PARTY DISCLOSURE

We do not share, sell, or transfer any personal information to third parties. The Extension only communicates with the ChromecastUltimate Android app that you install on your own device.

5. COOKIES

The Extension does not use cookies or similar tracking technologies.

6. DATA SECURITY

You are responsible for securing your local network and ensuring only trusted devices have access. The Extension connects to devices on your local network based on your configuration.

7. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY

The Extension is not intended for use by children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

8. CHANGES TO POLICY

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the "Last Updated" date above.

9. CONTACT

For questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact the Developer through the extension's support channels.

By using the Extension, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.